In past examples, we have used a fetched results controller. In this app, we create our own fetch request.\
\
Here's a list of predicate expressions that you could use in a fetch request:\
grade == 7\
grade < 9\
@sum.price > 1000\
firstName like[cd] 'mark'\
lastName contains[cd] 'blah'\
(firstName beginswith 'M') AND (children.firstName matches '*beth*')\
\
[cd] means case and diacritic, insensitive \
\
"matches" is not supported in Core Data, but it is supported in memory (so you can fetch to an array, and look for matches in that)\
\
Core Data supports only one one-to-many operation per query\
Therefore, can only be one of: ANY, ALL, IN \
